<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title><%= title %> | Deployment Flow</title>

    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@300;400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: "Poppins", sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            background: #f7f9fc;
        }

        header {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #0c4b32, #17833a);
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 60px 20px;
        }

        header h1 {
            margin: 0;
            font-size: 3rem;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        header p {
            margin-top: 10px;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            opacity: 0.9;
        }

        .section {
            padding: 50px 20px;
            max-width: 1100px;
            margin: auto;
        }

        .section h2 {
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            color: #0c4b32;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .section p {
            line-height: 1.7;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: #333;
        }

        .flow-container {
            margin-top: 40px;
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
            gap: 25px;
        }

        .flow-card {
            background: white;
            padding: 25px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
            transition: 0.3s ease;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .flow-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-6px);
            box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
        }

        .flow-card img {
            width: 70px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .code-block {
            background: #0e1a14;
            color: #00ff9c;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin-top: 25px;
            overflow-x: scroll;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        footer {
            background: #0c4b32;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
            margin-top: 40px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            header h1 {
                font-size: 2.3rem;
            }
            .section h2 {
                font-size: 1.8rem;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>About My Deployment Flow</h1>
    <p>Fully automated CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions, Docker, AWS ECR, ECS Fargate & Load Balancer</p>
</header>

<section class="section">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
        This project is deployed using a complete CI/CD pipeline.  
        Every push to the <strong>main</strong> branch automatically builds a Docker image, pushes it to 
        Amazon ECR, updates the ECS task definition, and redeploys the service behind an Application Load Balancer.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <h2>Deployment Flow</h2>

    <div class="flow-container">
        
        <div class="flow-card">
            <img src="https://i.ibb.co/Kz0Sgbt/github.png" alt="GitHub">
            <h3>1. GitHub Actions</h3>
            <p>
                Push to main triggers the workflow.  
                GitHub Actions builds the Docker image and runs the deployment steps.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-card">
            <img src="https://i.ibb.co/1KFfF29/docker.png" alt="Docker">
            <h3>2. Docker Image Build</h3>
            <p>
                GitHub builds a fresh Docker image of the project using your Dockerfile.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-card">
            <img src="https://i.ibb.co/KsNYnVz/aws-ecr.png" alt="ECR">
            <h3>3. Amazon ECR</h3>
            <p>
                The Docker image is pushed to Amazon ECR (Elastic Container Registry).
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-card">
            <img src="https://i.ibb.co/2kKXzWM/task.png" alt="Task">
            <h3>4. ECS Task Definition</h3>
            <p>
                Task definition is automatically updated with the new image tag.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-card">
            <img src="https://i.ibb.co/KwKyBj8/ecs.png" alt="ECS">
            <h3>5. ECS Fargate</h3>
            <p>
                ECS deploys the updated task across Fargate serverless compute.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-card">
            <img src="https://i.ibb.co/4JQZcZW/lb.png" alt="Load Balancer">
            <h3>6. Load Balancer</h3>
            <p>
                Traffic is routed through an Application Load Balancer ensuring 24/7 availability.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <h2>GitHub Actions Workflow</h2>

    <div class="code-block">
<pre>
<code>
<%= `name: Deploy to Amazon ECS

on:
  push:
    branches: [ "main" ]

env:
  AWS_REGION: ap-south-1
  ECR_REPOSITORY: node/mk-pipeline
  ECS_SERVICE: mk-task-definition-service-8pqtz7f5
  ECS_CLUSTER: mk-cluster
  ECS_TASK_DEFINITION: .aws/task-definition.json
  CONTAINER_NAME: mk-container

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v1
        with:
          aws-access-key-id: \${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}
          aws-secret-access-key: \${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}
          aws-region: \${{ env.AWS_REGION }}

      - uses: aws-actions/amazon-ecr-login@v1

      - name: Build Docker Image
        run: |
          docker build -t.... (trimmed)
` %>
</code>
</pre>
    </div>
</section>

<footer>
    © <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> My Deployment System — Powered by AWS & GitHub Actions
</footer>

</body>
</html>
